CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 26, 1955, pg. 4 reads: "County Scores 'Hit' - County detectives raided what they believe is an important numbers headquarters on the first floor of this house at 2604 Webster Avenue, Monday night, and arrested five male suspects. Detective Michael Matsey said numbers slips, confiscated in raid, indicated a yearly operation of approximately $500,000. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Three story brick row house with mansard roof, 2604 Webster Avenue, Crawford-Roberts
